01:22:11,009 --> 01:22:13,427
This is your basic breakdown
of the pitches,

1225
01:22:13,595 --> 01:22:15,804
where you should
be hitting them, why.

1226
01:22:15,972 --> 01:22:19,516
So you want us to walk more?
Good question. Yes.

1227
01:22:20,936 --> 01:22:23,020
Mr. Justice.

1228
01:22:23,188 --> 01:22:25,147
Had a few thoughts.
Yeah?

1229
01:22:25,315 --> 01:22:27,691
Yeah.
Gonna teach me some things?

1230
01:22:28,151 --> 01:22:29,860
Excuse me?

1231
01:22:31,404 --> 01:22:33,697
Never seen a GM
talk to players like that.

1232
01:22:33,865 --> 01:22:36,533
You never seen a GM
who was a player.

1233
01:22:38,286 --> 01:22:39,662
Huh.

1234
01:22:42,832 --> 01:22:45,626
We got a problem, David?
No, it's okay.

1235
01:22:45,794 --> 01:22:48,003
I know your routine.

1236
01:22:48,171 --> 01:22:50,464
It's patter. It's for effect.

1237
01:22:52,717 --> 01:22:56,887
But it's for them, all right?
That shit ain't for me.

1238
01:22:57,389 --> 01:22:59,139
Oh, you're special?

1239
01:23:01,559 --> 01:23:06,188
You're paying me 7 million bucks
a year, man, so, yeah,

1240
01:23:06,356 --> 01:23:08,691
maybe I am, a little bit.

1241
01:23:08,858 --> 01:23:11,819
No, man,
I ain't paying you 7.

1242
01:23:12,529 --> 01:23:14,405
Yankees are paying
half your salary.

1243
01:23:14,572 --> 01:23:17,408
That's what the New York Yankees
think of you.

1244
01:23:18,243 --> 01:23:22,579
They're paying you $3.5 million
to play against them.

1245
01:23:23,873 --> 01:23:26,041
Where you going with this, Billy?

1246
01:23:26,835 --> 01:23:29,169
David, you're 37.

1247
01:23:29,337 --> 01:23:33,090
How about you and I be honest about
what each of us want out of this?

1248
01:23:34,718 --> 01:23:38,095
I wanna milk the last ounce
of baseball you got in you.

1249
01:23:38,263 --> 01:23:40,556
And you wanna stay in the show.

1250
01:23:41,099 --> 01:23:43,058
Let's do that.

1251
01:23:43,935 --> 01:23:46,520
I'm not paying you
for the player you used to be.

1252
01:23:46,688 --> 01:23:49,690
I'm paying you for the player
you are right now.

1253
01:23:49,858 --> 01:23:53,277
You're smart. You get what
we're trying to do here.

1254
01:23:53,445 --> 01:23:56,280
Make an example
for the younger guys.

1255
01:23:56,448 --> 01:23:58,240
Be a leader.

1256
01:23:58,908 --> 01:24:00,576
Can you do that?

1257
01:24:07,667 --> 01:24:10,627
All right. I got you.

1258
01:24:13,089 --> 01:24:14,798
We're cool?

1259
01:24:16,885 --> 01:24:18,343
We're cool.

1260
01:24:23,641 --> 01:24:24,850
Scotty H.

1261
01:24:25,018 --> 01:24:27,144
Yo, what's up, D.J.?
Picking machine.

1262
01:24:28,521 --> 01:24:30,731
How you liking
first base, man?

1263
01:24:32,025 --> 01:24:35,235
It's coming along.
Picking it up.

1264
01:24:35,403 --> 01:24:39,531
You know, tough transition,
but I'm starting to feel better with it.

1265
01:24:39,699 --> 01:24:41,742
Yeah?
Yeah.

1266
01:24:41,910 --> 01:24:43,827
What's your biggest fear?

1267
01:24:44,454 --> 01:24:47,164
A baseball being hit
in my general direction.

1268
01:24:49,250 --> 01:24:52,377
That's funny.
Seriously, what is it?

1269
01:24:55,840 --> 01:24:58,175
No, seriously, that is.

1270
01:25:08,937 --> 01:25:11,271
Well, hey, good luck with that.

1271
01:25:11,439 --> 01:25:13,607
Be social out there.

1272
01:25:14,526 --> 01:25:17,069
Social.
Social. Like a greeter at the Gap.

1273
01:25:17,237 --> 01:25:19,321
Guy steps into your office,
chat him up.

1274
01:25:19,489 --> 01:25:22,157
You're well-read.
You went to school.

1275
01:25:22,325 --> 01:25:24,493
Yeah.
Have some fun. Relax.

1276
01:25:24,661 --> 01:25:27,538
Everyone wants to attack.
Quit trying to attack.

1277
01:25:27,705 --> 01:25:30,958
Let the game come to you, man.
There's no clock on this thing.

1278
01:25:31,126 --> 01:25:32,543
This is a war of attrition.

1279
01:25:32,710 --> 01:25:37,131
If I take more, I could even take a
few strikes, but I'll get walked more.

1280
01:25:37,298 --> 01:25:41,051
You get on base, we win.
You don't, we lose.

1281
01:25:41,219 --> 01:25:44,555
And I hate losing,
Chavvie. I hate it.

1282
01:25:44,722 --> 01:25:47,307
I hate losing more
than I even wanna win.

1283
01:25:47,475 --> 01:25:48,809
And there's
a difference.

1284
01:25:48,977 --> 01:25:50,477
No bunts.
Bunts is an out.

1285
01:25:50,645 --> 01:25:53,897
Even if the third baseman is back?
No bunting whatsoever.

1286
01:25:54,065 --> 01:25:56,817
If someone bunts on us,
throw it to first.

1287
01:25:56,985 --> 01:25:58,735
Don't be a hero
and go to second.

1288
01:25:58,903 --> 01:26:00,320
Let them make the mistakes.

1289
01:26:00,488 --> 01:26:03,407
When your enemy's making
mistakes, don't interrupt them.

1290
01:26:03,575 --> 01:26:06,118
They're giving you an out.
Just giving it to you.

1291
01:26:06,286 --> 01:26:07,578
Take it.
Say thank you.

1292
01:26:07,745 --> 01:26:09,746
Another thing.
No more stealing.

1293
01:26:09,914 --> 01:26:11,957
That's what I do,
what you pay me to do.

1294
01:26:12,125 --> 01:26:15,085
I pay you to get on first,
not get thrown out at second.

1295
01:26:15,253 --> 01:26:20,215
This is a process. It's a
process, it's a process. Okay?

1296
01:26:32,562 --> 01:26:36,440
Jason takes it, goes to second for
the only out, and the A's get a run.

1297
01:26:38,067 --> 01:26:42,154
Jermaine Dye homers again,
his second in two games.

1298
01:26:42,322 --> 01:26:46,783
And the A's are still hanging in.
We'll get you scores here.

1299
01:26:46,951 --> 01:26:51,413
The A's pull within two of the
Angels for the wild-card chase.

1300
01:26:51,581 --> 01:26:53,749
The Reds have now dropped
five in a row

1301
01:26:53,917 --> 01:26:57,294
as Oakland beats them
in the beginning of this series 5 to 3.

1302
01:26:57,462 --> 01:26:58,795
Tejada walks.

1303
01:26:58,963 --> 01:27:00,297
Ball four.

1304
01:27:00,465 --> 01:27:03,342
Ball four and Hatteberg walks.

1305
01:27:04,886 --> 01:27:08,388
What is happening in Oakland?
The A's have won seven in a row.

1306
01:27:08,556 --> 01:27:10,807
A lot of excitement.
What a winning streak.

1307
01:27:10,975 --> 01:27:13,810
But how about the calming
influence of Art Howe?

1308
01:27:13,978 --> 01:27:17,606
When you say "your source," if it's
not me or Peter, they don't know.

1309
01:27:17,774 --> 01:27:19,483
He's managing
an unorthodox team.

1310
01:27:19,651 --> 01:27:21,443
Right.
It's not a perfect roster.

1311
01:27:21,611 --> 01:27:24,905
But right now, Art Howe is
the reason this team is winning.

1312
01:27:25,073 --> 01:27:27,658
He deserves the credit.
Great, thanks. Bye.

1313
01:27:27,825 --> 01:27:29,368
Did you hear that?

1314
01:27:29,535 --> 01:27:32,496
I heard "seven in a row. "
You get the Cleveland matchups?

1315
01:27:32,664 --> 01:27:34,581
Yeah, right here.

1316
01:27:42,340 --> 01:27:43,799
Voos.
Billy.

1317
01:27:43,967 --> 01:27:47,219
That smell is getting worse.
I'm on it.

1318
01:27:47,971 --> 01:27:50,138
What are we doing?
Splitting it in half?

1319
01:27:50,306 --> 01:27:52,140
Both sides of the plate.
Got it.

1320
01:27:52,850 --> 01:27:55,018
Huddy. Mix it up.
Yes, sir.

1321
01:27:55,186 --> 01:27:57,354
Trust your slider, yeah?
Yes, sir.

1322
01:27:57,522 --> 01:27:59,523
You guys quit distracting him.

1323
01:27:59,691 --> 01:28:02,401
You couldn't hit that shit
last night with a paddle.

1324
01:28:02,568 --> 01:28:04,403
You gotta see more pitches.

1325
01:28:04,570 --> 01:28:07,072
All right, Billy.
Patience.

1326
01:28:10,868 --> 01:28:12,494
Hey, David.
Hey, Billy.

1327
01:28:12,662 --> 01:28:14,037
Great at bats.
Thank you.

1328
01:28:14,205 --> 01:28:15,747
Really quality.
Thank you.

1329
01:28:15,915 --> 01:28:18,625
Base hit to right field.
Tejada scores.

1330
01:28:18,793 --> 01:28:21,670
Chavez coming in.
The ball gets past Guiel.

1331
01:28:22,588 --> 01:28:26,717
The A's, from 5-nothing down,
now lead 6 to 5.

1332
01:28:36,728 --> 01:28:39,730
The Oakland A's are completely
out of hand at the moment.

1333
01:28:39,897 --> 01:28:42,566
They are an AL-best 17 and 4
this month.

1334
01:28:42,734 --> 01:28:46,528
They also took back-to-back series
at Boston and at New York.

1335
01:28:46,696 --> 01:28:49,323
Remember when they traded
Jeremy Giambi in June

1336
01:28:49,490 --> 01:28:51,825
and everyone thought
they'd just given up?

1337
01:28:51,993 --> 01:28:54,661
Actually, not so much.

1338
01:28:58,750 --> 01:29:01,251
Suzanne, get Shapiro on the phone.

1339
01:29:01,753 --> 01:29:04,921
You thinking Rincon?
His season's done. He's lost faith.

1340
01:29:05,089 --> 01:29:08,091
I think he's gonna dump him.
Hard-core.

1341
01:29:08,259 --> 01:29:10,552
Shapiro on 2.

1342
01:29:12,096 --> 01:29:13,889
Mark, Billy. Let's be honest.

1343
01:29:14,057 --> 01:29:17,434
A premier setup man isn't gonna
get you closer to the play-offs.

1344
01:29:17,602 --> 01:29:19,519
Are you referring to Rincon?

1345
01:29:19,687 --> 01:29:21,688
He's a luxury
you can't afford, man.

1346
01:29:21,856 --> 01:29:24,566
And you can? There's half
a million on his contract.

1347
01:29:24,734 --> 01:29:26,777
And we've got
at least one other suitor.

1348
01:29:26,944 --> 01:29:29,654
By "at least one," you mean one.

1349
01:29:29,822 --> 01:29:32,282
Who is it?
I'd rather not say.

1350
01:29:32,450 --> 01:29:34,785
San Francisco.
San Francisco.

1351
01:29:34,952 --> 01:29:36,453
I'll call you back.

1352
01:29:38,247 --> 01:29:40,415
What do you think
we can get for Magnante?

1353
01:29:40,583 --> 01:29:41,833
Nothing.

1354
01:29:42,752 --> 01:29:45,796
What's left on Venafro's contract?
Two seventy-five.

1355
01:29:46,631 --> 01:29:48,423
Suzanne,
get me Sabean on the line.

1356
01:29:48,591 --> 01:29:52,677
Get the Giants interested in Venafro,
Mark's only got one buyer for Rincon.

1357
01:29:52,845 --> 01:29:54,304
Us.
On 3.

1358
01:29:56,349 --> 01:29:59,810
Saby-Sabster, it's Billy.
What do you think of Venafro?

1359
01:29:59,977 --> 01:30:02,145
I can let you have him
for almost nothing.

1360
01:30:02,313 --> 01:30:04,898
Why would you do that?
Because I'm amazing.

1361
01:30:05,066 --> 01:30:07,067
I want a couple bucks
and a sweetener.

1362
01:30:07,485 --> 01:30:09,319
Throw in, say...

1363
01:30:09,487 --> 01:30:11,655
Anderson.
Anderson.

1364
01:30:11,823 --> 01:30:14,783
I like Anderson.
No, you don't. Nobody likes him.

1365
01:30:14,951 --> 01:30:17,494
I don't know why I'm doing this.
But let's do it.

1366
01:30:17,662 --> 01:30:20,580
Venafro for Michaelson. Anderson.
I don't know his name.

1367
01:30:20,748 --> 01:30:23,625
I'll think about it.
Think about it and call me back.

1368
01:30:24,168 --> 01:30:26,169
Get Shapiro on.

1369
01:30:34,095 --> 01:30:36,346
Shapiro's on 2.

1370
01:30:38,391 --> 01:30:40,350
Mark.
You can't afford him, Billy.

1371
01:30:40,518 --> 01:30:41,601
You sure about that?

1372
01:30:41,769 --> 01:30:44,354
I get the impression
the market for Rincon is softening.

1373
01:30:44,522 --> 01:30:46,148
Huh?
I could be wrong,

1374
01:30:46,315 --> 01:30:47,941
but I'd call whoever's
interested

1375
01:30:48,109 --> 01:30:51,611
and see if they're still interested.
Call me back.

1376
01:30:52,488 --> 01:30:55,866
What about the Mets for Venafro?
You offered him to the Giants.

1377
01:30:56,033 --> 01:30:57,701
Suzanne, Steve Phillips.

1378
01:30:57,869 --> 01:31:02,706
